ecently.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042133,0.089133,0.10258,0.10169,0.097002,0.094732,0.093381,0.090524,0.086169,0.082258,0.072462,0.047936],"unified_progress":[0.058954,0.089948,0.089571,0.094495,0.098095,0.096072,0.09291,0.095163,0.088947,0.083475,0.067939,0.044432]},{"section":6,"text":"His vitals are normal, and during an episode, the EEG shows three-per-second spike and wave discharge.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0398,0.077637,0.096802,0.11006,0.11166,0.11002,0.10537,0.094007,0.080386,0.068647,0.059318,0.046299],"unified_progress":[0.046015,0.081805,0.094464,0.10264,0.10641,0.10095,0.09744,0.091269,0.094873,0.075201,0.062402,0.046526]},{"section":7,"text":"First, the episodes are brief, which makes me think it's something that doesn't last too long.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.06147,0.095863,0.093378,0.098757,0.090221,0.087592,0.090621,0.083152,0.080039,0.084168,0.074071,0.060668],"unified_progress":[0.050487,0.078984,0.087315,0.096258,0.096115,0.093111,0.095797,0.093049,0.0879,0.088869,0.073447,0.058667]},{"section":8,"text":"The fact that he stops responding and stares could be a sign of a seizure, but the mother didn't mention any other symptoms like twitching or falling.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.06483,0.10097,0.097483,0.093319,0.086192,0.085019,0.086039,0.08471,0.082803,0.081288,0.077174,0.060177],"unified_progress":[0.06662,0.089147,0.08647,0.085853,0.089147,0.090588,0.089829,0.095351,0.089046,0.087735,0.074824,0.055391]},{"section":9,"text":"However, the EEG showing spike and wave discharges is a key clue.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.058515,0.073135,0.084841,0.094806,0.093763,0.093278,0.094087,0.088143,0.084103,0.081859,0.079091,0.074378],"unified_progress":[0.049356,0.069705,0.08095,0.089931,0.093946,0.093255,0.094673,0.091894,0.092602,0.088519,0.081361,0.073805]},{"section":10,"text":"Spike-wave complexes are typically associated with a specific type of seizure called the \"spike and wave complex,\" which is common in childhood.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030193,0.049164,0.069031,0.082112,0.098279,0.10589,0.10888,0.11124,0.10701,0.09318,0.07608,0.068944],"unified_progress":[0.029474,0.05524,0.08041,0.092245,0.098975,0.11543,0.10636,0.10298,0.097108,0.090978,0.073581,0.057218]},{"section":11,"text":"I remember that this complex is often linked to a benign condition.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037069,0.062358,0.072645,0.082773,0.089914,0.094595,0.099866,0.10057,0.099137,0.098747,0.085858,0.076469],"unified_progress":[0.032453,0.060874,0.078199,0.092166,0.096617,0.10069,0.10139,0.10071,0.096687,0.093445,0.080117,0.066653]},{"section":12,"text":"The most common one I can think of is the benign Rolandic epilepsy, also known as the \"salaam convulsion.\"","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029063,0.052008,0.067396,0.079033,0.092156,0.09989,0.10511,0.10865,0.10738,0.099276,0.084739,0.075292],"unified_progress":[0.029684,0.057156,0.07695,0.090567,0.097357,0.10629,0.10485,0.10304,0.098494,0.093796,0.078095,0.063717]},{"section":13,"text":"This usually starts between 3-5 years of age, which fits here since the child is 5.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04297,0.067337,0.07585,0.080719,0.087169,0.092323,0.097393,0.099784,0.099826,0.0965,0.085237,0.074891],"unified_progress":[0.050312,0.072265,0.079632,0.086638,0.091539,0.097615,0.09643,0.098257,0.093542,0.090698,0.078049,0.065022]},{"section":14,"text":"It's characterized by brief episodes of staring, unresponsiveness, and sometimes eye blinking, which matches the description.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049115,0.083965,0.082291,0.086998,0.085598,0.08924,0.093187,0.094588,0.093245,0.085897,0.079689,0.076187],"unified_progress":[0.057484,0.082025,0.087081,0.08824,0.08997,0.09769,0.093189,0.095902,0.088992,0.084166,0.073192,0.062071]},{"section":15,"text":"The fact that his milestones were normal and there's no history of other illnesses makes me lean towards a benign condition.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036239,0.060156,0.073424,0.077462,0.080707,0.08517,0.089527,0.094965,0.098524,0.10316,0.10379,0.096881],"unified_progress":[0.039887,0.060862,0.068981,0.076423,0.084745,0.08844,0.091394,0.098399,0.098795,0.10504,0.098198,0.088838]},{"section":16,"text":"The EEG findings support this because they show the characteristic spike and wave pattern, which is typical for Rolandic epilepsy.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036243,0.042285,0.056147,0.066141,0.074574,0.080961,0.085892,0.091321,0.096592,0.10184,0.11722,0.15078],"unified_progress":[0.031509,0.045273,0.058584,0.068373,0.074947,0.0834,0.085749,0.091894,0.097403,0.10047,0.11751,0.14489]},{"section":17,"text":"There's no mention of any other neurological issues, so this seems like the most likely diagnosis.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021913,0.042623,0.058795,0.067517,0.073571,0.081542,0.089321,0.10002,0.10847,0.11921,0.12379,0.11323],"unified_progress":[0.022612,0.043459,0.056558,0.06639,0.07745,0.083969,0.091664,0.10318,0.10934,0.12402,0.11636,0.10499]},{"section":18,"text":"The most likely diagnosis is **Benign Rolandic Epilepsy**.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019532,0.038397,0.04646,0.053799,0.059251,0.065747,0.074657,0.083557,0.095683,0.11317,0.14393,0.20582],"unified_progress":[0.017775,0.035269,0.045224,0.055325,0.061223,0.071722,0.077726,0.087774,0.096968,0.10803,0.14259,0.20037]},{"section":19,"text":"The presentation of brief episodes, normal development, and the EEG findings of spike and wave complexes are characteristic of this condition.","dimens